-(DOM): Document Object Model

Six Global DOM Objects
1.Document- Current HTML page and its content
2.History- List of pages the user last visited
3.Location- URL of the current HTML page
4.Navigator- Info about the web browser used
5.Screen- Info about the screen area occupied
          by the user
6.Window-The browser window

Window object
-The top level object in DOM hierarchy
-Properties: document, history, location, name
-Method: alert,confirm, prompt
        setInterval, setTimeout, clearInterval,
        clearTimeout
        open, close
        blur, focus, moveBy, moveTo, print, resizeBy,
        resizeTo, scrollBy, scrollTo,

Document object
-The current webpage and elements inside it 
-Properties: anchors, body, cookie, domain, forms,
             images, links, referrer, title, URL
-Methods: getElementByID, getElementsByname,
          getElementsByTagName
          close, open, write, writeln
          
Location object
-The URL of the current web page
-Properties: host, hostname, href, pathname,
             port, protocol, search
-Methods: assign, reload, replace

Navigator object 
-Information about the web browser application
-Properties: appName, appVersion, browserLanguage,
             cookieEnabled, platform, userAgent
             
Screen object
-Information about the client's display screen
-Properties: availHeight, availWidth, colorDepth,
             height, pixelDepth, width

History object
-The list of sites the browser visited in this window
-Properties: length
-Methods: back, forward, go

Goal as a Web developer
-Write an unobstrusive JS code
-Make a disctinction for the website
  a. content (HTML)
  b. presentation (CSS)
  c. behavior (JavaScript)
